description:
&lt;p&gt;Chemotherapy services at Frimley Health NHS Foundation Trust is growing and moving forward with ambitious plans and major investment in our people and facilities! It’s an exciting time to join us and grow as a professional – while playing your part in the delivery of first class cancer care.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Eden Day Unit, based at Wexham Park Hospital, is an extremely busy and friendly chemotherapy day unit, providing chemotherapy and immunotherapy for patients with all types of cancers. We have just recently undergone an extensive refurbishment programme and we are able to provide excellent care in a wonderful, brand new facility.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The nursing team works extremely closely with all members of the MDT for all tumour groups and we deliver a robust, professional nurse led service. We are incredibly fortunate in that the nursing team has been adopted by Macmillan Cancer Care, and therefore the post is branded as a Macmillan Professional enabling each member of staff to access an individual education grant of £1000 each per year&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are a newly qualified nurse , a nurse with experience of working in an acute trust or a nurse with existing chemotherapy / cancer experience looking for an opportunity to develop your skills and knowledge within cancer and chemotherapy services, then we would love to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Frimley Health will support you to complete the accredited course in chemotherapy nursing practice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We will guarantee you a place on the Principles in Cancer Care Module that is an in house run , accredited module facilitated by (UWL)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Macmillan On line training programmes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities to work alongside site specific clinical nurse specialists to enhance and enable further development into this field of practice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Newly qualified nurses will be offered a bespoke 12 month preceptor -ship programme with 14 protected study days.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking forward to hearing from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Claire James – Matron / Lead Chemotherapy Nurse &lt;br /&gt;Claire.james25@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
